A gang staged a daring raid at Mwiria coffee factory in Embu North sub-county and stole coffee worth Sh1.5 million on Thursday night.
  A committee member, John Rutere, said agro-chemicals worth Sh300, 000 that was to be distributed to farmers, a generator and power saw were also stolen. 
 ALSO READ:

'Dead' boy returns home

 The robbers took two computers and record books that contained crucial information relating to an ongoing inquiry into loss of money in the parent Central Ngandori Cooperative Society.
 "We suspect the theft is meant to derail the ongoing inquiry into the malpractices that happened in the society leading to loss of money from sale of coffee and failure to pay farmers their dues.
