 However, the stolen documents will not affect the inquiry," said Rutere. The assailants broke into the factory at around midnight and tied up two guards before loading the 2,480 kilos of coffee beans in the stores, drying tables and packed them into a vehicle and fled.
 Mr Rutere said the guards raised the alarm at around 2pm after the thugs had left. The theft was reported at Manyatta Police Station. Area OCPD Mark Wanjala visited the factory as part of their investigations. 
